## v1.1.0 — 2026-06-19

- Version: 1.1.0 (minor)
- Date: 2026-06-19
- Changed by: re-plan of ProjectAgamemnon #263 after reviewer NOGO
- Verification: unverified (still a planning artifact — no code built or tested)

### What changed

Added five new durable learnings and three new Failed Attempts rows that surfaced
during the NOGO-remediation re-plan of ProjectAgamemnon issue #263:

1. Caller fan-out has a glob blind spot — enumerate every `grep` hit by file:line,
   never describe the fan-out by a narrowing filename glob; finish with a confirming
   re-grep for zero remaining old-arity sites.
2. Test fixtures have heterogeneous ownership patterns (stack member vs. heap
   inline-static pointer) — each needs a bespoke edit matching its existing lifetime
   style, not a copy-paste.
3. A test that asserts only the message SUBJECT does not verify field-level
   acceptance criteria — extend the test double to capture the full payload and
   assert each literal field (plus a negative assertion that timestamp is absent
   from metadata).
4. Extending a shared test double is a mini fan-out of its own — grep every reader
   of the changed member and migrate them.
5. Reviewer-trust signal — honestly self-disclosing unverified assumptions in the
   plan downgraded two would-be majors to recoverable minors.

Also added a Risks subsection capturing the uncertain/unverified reliances of the
re-plan (line drift, uncompiled fake-struct change, assumed httplib Request field
names, unverified validator section names).

### Why

The first plan (v1.0.0) received a reviewer NOGO. The specific gaps — a glob that
would have missed callers, a subject-only test that did not verify required field
contents, and an assumption that all fixtures share one DI lifetime style — are
reusable planning lessons that must not be lost. v1.1.0 records them so the next
planner avoids the same NOGO.

